{
  "key_path": "RolePortalAdminDescription",
  "content": "{{productName}} admins can access {{productName}} settings, manage and archive rooms, invite new users and assign roles below their level. All admins have access to the {{sectionName}} section.<br/> <1>In {{agentSection}}</1>: can create, configure and manage {{agentSection}}, including their knowledge base and access settings.",
  "content_en_sha1_hash": "bab4e02ce9aa9451d52b5912286876ff2522a52d",
  "created_at": "2025-12-16T07:24:33.027Z",
  "updated_at": "2026-04-13T08:35:42.804Z",
  "comment": {
    "text": "This is a description of the Portal Admin role, displayed when viewing user roles or assigning a new role. It explains the permissions of a Portal Admin, including managing rooms, inviting users, and accessing settings. `{{productName}}` is the product name (e.g., ONLYOFFICE DocSpace), `{{sectionName}}` is the name of a specific section, and `{{agentSection}}` refers to a section related to agents. The `<1>` tag bolds the text within it.",
    "is_auto": true,
